ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: STAT 645 is an excellent class and I would definitely recommend it to a fellow student. Students primarily learn about HMM and MCMC methods and their applications to biology. There are two difficult problem sets and a final project with a presentation. The course is an excellent balance between the theoretical and the applied. You learn the math behind the techniques as well as how to execute the techniques with dynamic programming. I would only recommend the class for someone with a strong background in statistics and practice in R.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The class strengthened my understanding of different statistical approaches and demonstrated ways to apply them outside of my primary field of study.
